{"parentUuid":"abfe222a-a1f7-4dd8-9a45-efb1b7d43c95","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\johnm\\gradeBot\\teacher-grade-agent","sessionId":"ffca678e-2785-440e-b7d2-13e8c6423da1","version":"2.1.50","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"stateless-jumping-blossom","type":"progress","data":{"message":{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VcALXr7BgAd3ab6EeDRPRM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# TeacherGradeAgent\n     2→\n     3→Local-first, production-grade AI assistant for teachers. It receives WhatsApp grade-sheet photos, performs OCR using local Ollama (`qwen3-vl:30b`), asks for explicit confirmation, updates Excel safely with backups, generates PDF reports, and replies on WhatsApp.\n     4→\n     5→## Features\n     6→\n     7→- Local-only after setup (no cloud API)\n     8→- WhatsApp MD via `neonize` (QR pairing once)\n     9→- Multimodal OCR using `qwen3-vl:30b`\n    10→- LangGraph stateful workflow (planning, tool routing, retries)\n    11→- Strict confirmation gate before any Excel write\n    12→- SQLAlchemy + SQLite memory and audit logs\n    13→- Backup before every workbook mutation\n    14→- Structured logging to console + file\n    15→- Health endpoint at `http://127.0.0.1:18789/healthz`\n    16→- Anti-spam rate limiting per teacher\n    17→- CLI: `start`, `status`, `backup`\n    18→- Optional Docker and systemd service\n    19→\n    20→## Project layout\n    21→\n    22→```text\n    23→teacher-grade-agent/\n    24→├── config.yaml\n    25→├── requirements.txt\n    26→├── Dockerfile\n    27→├── docker-compose.yml\n    28→├── main.py\n    29→├── README.md\n    30→├── .env.example\n    31→├── src/\n    32→│   ├── __init__.py\n    33→│   ├── config.py\n    34→│   ├── whatsapp/\n    35→│   │   ├── client.py\n    36→│   │   └── handlers.py\n    37→│   ├── agent/\n    38→│   │   ├── graph.py\n    39→│   │   ├── tools.py\n    40→│   │   ├── prompts.py\n    41→│   │   └── state.py\n    42→│   ├── tools/\n    43→│   │   ├── vision_ocr.py\n    44→│   │   ├── excel_handler.py\n    45→│   │   ├── report_generator.py\n    46→│   │   └── utils.py\n    47→│   └── db/\n    48→│       └── models.py\n    49→└── skills/\n    50→```\n    51→\n    52→## 1) Installation and setup\n    53→\n    54→### A. Prerequisites\n    55→\n    56→- Python 3.12+\n    57→- Ollama installed locally\n    58→- WhatsApp account on phone (for QR pair)\n    59→\n    60→### B. Install dependencies\n    61→\n    62→```bash\n    63→cd teacher-grade-agent\n    64→python -m venv .venv\n    65→# Windows\n    66→.venv\\Scripts\\activate\n    67→# macOS/Linux\n    68→# source .venv/bin/activate\n    69→pip install -r requirements.txt\n    70→```\n    71→\n    72→### C. Setup Ollama model (`qwen3-vl:30b`)\n    73→\n    74→```bash\n    75→ollama pull qwen3-vl:30b\n    76→ollama serve\n    77→```\n    78→\n    79→Verify model is available:\n    80→\n    81→```bash\n    82→ollama list\n    83→```\n    84→\n    85→Expected model line should include `qwen3-vl:30b`.\n    86→\n    87→### D. Configure app\n    88→\n    89→1. Review `config.yaml`.\n    90→2. Optionally copy `.env.example` to `.env` and set overrides.\n    91→3. Place/prepare teacher Excel templates under `data/excel/` (or leave auto-create enabled).\n    92→\n    93→## 2) Start and run\n    94→\n    95→### Start service\n    96→\n    97→```bash\n    98→python main.py start\n    99→```\n   100→\n   101→On first run, neonize will request WhatsApp pairing (QR/pair status in logs). Pair once from your phone.\n   102→\n   103→### Check status\n   104→\n   105→```bash\n   106→python main.py status\n   107→```\n   108→\n   109→### Manual backup\n   110→\n   111→```bash\n   112→python main.py backup\n   113→```\n   114→\n   115→## WhatsApp workflow\n   116→\n   117→1. Teacher sends a grade-sheet photo.\n   118→2. Agent extracts rows and replies with:\n   119→   - row count,\n   120→   - workbook/sheet target,\n   121→   - warnings,\n   122→   - confirmation token.\n   123→3. Teacher sends `confirm ABCD1234`.\n   124→4. Agent backs up workbook, writes rows, computes stats, generates PDF report.\n   125→5. Agent replies with write confirmation + report path.\n   126→\n   127→Cancel any pending write:\n   128→\n   129→```text\n   130→cancel ABCD1234\n   131→```\n   132→\n   133→## 3) Example conversation flow (with screenshot descriptions)\n   134→\n   135→- Screenshot 1 (teacher chat): a photo of handwritten score sheet is sent.\n   136→- Screenshot 2 (agent reply): \"Parsed grade sheet successfully... Reply with: confirm 9F2A1BCD\".\n   137→- Screenshot 3 (teacher): `confirm 9F2A1BCD`.\n   138→- Screenshot 4 (agent): \"Excel update confirmed... Rows written: 34... Report: data/reports/teacher_1_20260101_101122.pdf\".\n   139→\n   140→## 4) Per-teacher report customization\n   141→\n   142→Show current profile:\n   143→\n   144→```text\n   145→report profile\n   146→```\n   147→\n   148→Update toggles:\n   149→\n   150→```text\n   151→report set include_histogram=true,include_outliers=true,include_subject_averages=true\n   152→```\n   153→\n   154→These settings are stored per teacher in SQLite and applied to future reports.\n   155→\n   156→## 5) Add new skills later\n   157→\n   158→- Put new Python modules in `skills/`.\n   159→- Expose functions/classes with clear input/output contracts.\n   160→- Register new functionality as LangChain `StructuredTool` in `src/agent/tools.py`.\n   161→- Add routing logic in `src/agent/graph.py`.\n   162→- Add audit logging and confirmation if mutation is involved.\n   163→\n   164→## 6) Health endpoint\n   165→\n   166→- `GET http://127.0.0.1:18789/healthz`\n   167→- `GET http://127.0.0.1:18789/readyz`\n   168→\n   169→## 7) Docker (optional)\n   170→\n   171→```bash\n   172→docker compose up --build -d\n   173→```\n   174→\n   175→## 8) systemd example (Linux)\n   176→\n   177→Use the included template `teacher-grade-agent.service.example` or create `/etc/systemd/system/teacher-grade-agent.service`:\n   178→\n   179→```ini\n   180→[Unit]\n   181→Description=TeacherGradeAgent\n   182→After=network.target\n   183→\n   184→[Service]\n   185→Type=simple\n   186→User=YOUR_USER\n   187→WorkingDirectory=/opt/teacher-grade-agent\n   188→ExecStart=/opt/teacher-grade-agent/.venv/bin/python /opt/teacher-grade-agent/main.py start\n   189→Restart=always\n   190→RestartSec=5\n   191→Environment=TGA_CONFIG_PATH=/opt/teacher-grade-agent/config.yaml\n   192→\n   193→[Install]\n   194→WantedBy=multi-user.target\n   195→```\n   196→\n   197→Then:\n   198→\n   199→```bash\n   200→sudo systemctl daemon-reload\n   201→sudo systemctl enable teacher-grade-agent\n   202→sudo systemctl start teacher-grade-agent\n   203→sudo systemctl status teacher-grade-agent\n   204→```\n   205→\n   206→## Troubleshooting\n   207→\n   208→- Ollama down: start with `ollama serve` and verify `ollama list`.\n   209→- Model missing: run `ollama pull qwen3-vl:30b`.\n   210→- WhatsApp not connecting: remove stale session DB under `data/sessions/` and pair again.\n   211→- Excel write blocked: confirm template headers can map to required fields (`student_name`, `subject`, `score`).\n   212→- Too many messages warning: wait for rate-limit window to reset.\n   213→"}]},"uuid":"8aeb009e-d44b-4b5d-bccd-57f88accca18","timestamp":"2026-02-21T14:46:20.332Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"Explore the project at C:\\Users\\johnm\\gradeBot\\teacher-grade-agent thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. What kind of project this is (language, framework)\n2. How it's meant to be run (look for package.json, requirements.txt, Makefile, README, docker-compose, etc.)\n3. Any configuration files, environment variables, or setup steps required\n4. Entry points (main files, scripts, etc.)\n\nBe very thorough - check all config files, READMEs, and any documentation about running the project.","agentId":"a41935e9b6d71fcfa"},"toolUseID":"agent_msg_01LxXDkVGdWQ3uQGCDwaT1Gd","parentToolUseID":"t