{"parentUuid":"a03630d3-350b-4090-b86a-b3a6cc12faa4","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\johnm\\gradeBot\\teacher-grade-agent","sessionId":"ffca678e-2785-440e-b7d2-13e8c6423da1","version":"2.1.50","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"stateless-jumping-blossom","type":"progress","data":{"message":{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01957kfFzKznLvSXXD3Ap2hd","type":"tool_result","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport base64\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nfrom ollama import Client\nfrom PIL import Image\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, ValidationError\n\nfrom src.config import AppSettings\nfrom src.tools.utils import clamp\n\n\nclass GradeRow(BaseModel):\n    student_name: str\n    subject: str | None = None\n    score: float | None = None\n    max_score: float | None = None\n    total: float | None = None\n    remarks: str | None = None\n    row_confidence: float = 0.0\n\n\nclass GradeSheetExtraction(BaseModel):\n    teacher_hint: str | None = None\n    class_name: str | None = None\n    exam_name: str | None = None\n    date: str | None = None\n    rows: list[GradeRow] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    global_confidence: float = 0.0\n    warnings: list[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n\n\nclass VisionOCRTool:\n    def __init__(self, settings: AppSettings):\n        self.settings = settings\n        self.client = Client(host=settings.ollama.base_url)\n\n    def extract_from_image(self, image_path: Path, language_mode: str = \"en\") -> GradeSheetExtraction:\n        if not image_path.exists():\n            raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Image not found: {image_path}\")\n\n        # Ensure readable image and convert to RGB for stable OCR behavior.\n        image = Image.open(image_path).convert(\"RGB\")\n        with image_path.open(\"rb\") as file:\n            image_b64 = base64.b64encode(file.read()).decode(\"utf-8\")\n\n        system_prompt = self._system_prompt(language_mode)\n        user_prompt = self._user_prompt()\n\n        response = self.client.chat(\n            model=self.settings.ollama.model,\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                {\n                    \"role\": \"user\",\n                    \"content\": user_prompt,\n                    \"images\": [image_b64],\n                },\n            ],\n            options={\n                \"temperature\": self.settings.ollama.temperature,\n                \"num_predict\": 2048,\n            },\n        )\n        del image\n        raw_content = response.get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n\n        try:\n            extraction = self._parse_extraction(raw_content)\n        except ValueError:\n            extraction = self.repair_json(raw_content)\n        extraction.global_confidence = clamp(extraction.global_confidence)\n        extraction.rows = extraction.rows[: self.settings.agent.max_rows_per_image]\n        return extraction\n\n    def repair_json(self, malformed_json_text: str) -> GradeSheetExtraction:\n        repair_prompt = (\n            \"You receive malformed OCR JSON. Repair it into valid JSON only, matching this schema: \"\n            \"{teacher_hint,class_name,exam_name,date,rows:[{student_name,subject,score,max_score,total,remarks,row_confidence}],\"\n            \"global_confidence,warnings}.\"\n        )\n        response = self.client.chat(\n            model=self.settings.ollama.model,\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": repair_prompt},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": malformed_json_text},\n            ],\n            options={\"temperature\": 0.0, \"num_predict\": 2048},\n        )\n        raw_content = response.get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n        return self._parse_extraction(raw_content)\n\n    def _parse_extraction(self, raw_content: str) -> GradeSheetExtraction:\n        payload = self._coerce_json_payload(raw_content)\n        try:\n            extraction = GradeSheetExtraction.model_validate(payload)","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"1a691bef-dc1e-4814-a7c1-b164bfcbcc80","timestamp":"2026-02-21T14:46:28.759Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"Explore the project at C:\\Users\\johnm\\gradeBot\\teacher-grade-agent thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. What kind of project this is (language, framework)\n2. How it's meant to be run (look for package.json, requirements.txt, Makefile, README, docker-compose, etc.)\n3. Any configuration files, environment variables, or setup steps required\n4. Entry points (main files, scripts, etc.)\n\nBe very thorough - check all config files, READMEs, and any documentation about running the project.","agentId":"a41935e9b6d71fcfa"},"toolUseID":"agent_msg_01LxXDkVGdWQ3uQGCDwaT1Gd","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01X2mkb65cpRE1yXJNZQ1PMJ","uuid":"e25c513c-44e6-407f-a650-6dbeb9995168","timestamp":"2026-02-21T14:46:28.762Z"}
{"parentUuid":"609521ac-d62d-4138-bfc4-ba400baa1b69","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\johnm\\gradeBot\\teacher-grade-agent","sessionId":"ffca678e-2785-440e-b7d2-13e8c6423da1","version":"2.1.50","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"stateless-jumping-blossom","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X2mkb65cpRE1yXJNZQ1PMJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary of the project:\n\n## Project Exploration Summary\n\n### 1. **Project Type & Language**\n- **Language**: Python 3.12+\n- **Framework**: Multi-framework architecture:\n  - **LangGraph**: Stateful agentic workflow orchestration\n  - **FastAPI**: Health/readiness endpoints\n  - **LangChain**: Tool definition and integration\n  - **Neonize**: WhatsApp client (MD protocol)\n  - **Ollama**: Local multimodal AI (vision + language)\n\n### 2. **Purpose**\nTeacherGradeAgent is a **local-first, production-grade AI assistant for teachers** that:\n- Receives grade-sheet photos via WhatsApp\n- Performs OCR using locally-hosted `qwen3-vl:30b` model (multimodal vision-language)\n- Requests explicit confirmation before data mutations\n- Updates Excel workbooks with automatic backups\n- Generates PDF reports with customizable profiles\n- Replies via WhatsApp with confirmation and report paths\n\n### 3. **How to Run**\n\n#### Prerequisites\n- Python 3.12+\n- Ollama installed locally with `qwen3-vl:30b` model pulled\n- WhatsApp account (for QR pairing on first run)\n\n#### Installation Steps\n```bash\ncd teacher-grade-agent\npython -m venv .venv\n# Windows: .venv\\Scripts\\activate\n# macOS/Linux: source .venv/bin/activate\npip install -r requirements.txt\nollama pull qwen3-vl:30b\nollama serve  # in another terminal\n```\n\n#### Starting the Service\n```bash\npython main.py start     # Start service (auto-pairs WhatsApp on first run)\npython main.py status   # Check status\npython main.py backup   # Manual backup\n```\n\n#### Docker (Optional)\n```bash\ndocker compose up --build -d\n```\n\n#### Systemd Service (Linux, Optional)\nUse template file: `teacher-grade-agent.service.example`\n\n### 4. **Configuration Files & Environment Variables**\n\n#### Primary Config: `config.yaml`\nYAML-based hierarchical configuration covering:\n- App metadata (name, environment, timezone)\n- Directory paths (data, logs, reports, backups, excel, sessions, skills)\n- Database (SQLite path)\n- Ollama (base URL, model name, timeout, temperature)\n- WhatsApp (device name, session store, media dir, reconnect settings, admin numbers)\n- Rate limiting (30 messages per 300 seconds)\n- Agent settings (retries, OCR confidence threshold, pending action TTL, max rows per image)\n- Excel (workbook name, sheet name, required columns, auto-create flag)\n- Report generation (default PDF profile with toggles for cover, student table, histograms, etc.)\n- Logging (level, rotation, retention)\n- Health endpoint (enabled by default at 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n#### Environment Overrides: `.env.example`\nAll config settings can be overridden via environment variables prefixed with `TGA_`:\n- `TGA_CONFIG_PATH`\n- `TGA_OLLAMA_BASE_URL`, `TGA_OLLAMA_MODEL`\n- `TGA_DATABASE_SQLITE_PATH`\n- `TGA_PATHS_SESSION_DIR`, `TGA_PATHS_REPORTS_DIR`, `TGA_PATHS_EXCEL_DIR`\n- `TGA_LOGGING_LEVEL`\n- `TGA_AGENT_DEFAULT_LANGUAGE_MODE`\n- `TGA_HEALTH_ENABLED`, `TGA_HEALTH_HOST`, `TGA_HEALTH_PORT`\n\n### 5. **Entry Points & Directory Structure**\n\n#### Main Entry Point\n**`main.py`** - CLI application with three commands:\n- `start`: Launch the WhatsApp service (includes health server)\n- `status`: Check system health (DB, Ollama, model availability)\n- `backup`: Create manual backup of Excel files and audit logs\n\n#### Source Code Layout\n```\nsrc/\n├── config.py              # Settings loading (YAML + env overrides via Pydantic)\n├── whatsapp/\n│   ├── client.py         # Neonize-based WhatsApp client (event-driven)\n│   └── handlers.py       # Message processing & routing\n├── agent/\n│   ├── graph.py          # LangGraph workflow (7-node state machine)\n│   ├── tools.py          # LangChain StructuredTool definitions\n│   ├── prompts.py        # System/user prompts for planning & tooling\n│   └── state.py          # TypedDict schemas for agent state\n├── tools/\n│   ├── vision_ocr.py     # Ollama integration (qwen3-vl multimodal)\n│   ├── excel_handler.py  # XLSX read/write with backups\n│   ├── report_generator.py # PDF generation with matplotlib/fpdf2\n│   └── utils.py          # Helpers (token parsing, backups, etc.)\n└── db/\n    └── models.py         # SQLAlchemy ORM (Teacher, PendingAction, AuditLog)\n```\n\n#### Data Directory\nAll runtime artifacts stored in `./data/`:\n- `./data/excel/` - Teacher Excel workbooks\n- `./data/reports/` - Generated PDF reports\n- `./data/backups/` - Automatic & manual workbook backups\n- `./data/sessions/` - Neonize WhatsApp session DB and media\n- `./data/logs/` - Application logs (rotated, 14-day retention)\n- `./data/teacher_grade_agent.db` - SQLite (audit logs, teacher profiles, pending actions)\n\n#### Optional Skills Directory\n`./skills/` - Extensible Python modules for custom skills (registered in `src/agent/tools.py`)\n\n### 6. **Key Dependencies** (from requirements.txt)\n- **Core**: typer (CLI), pydantic (settings), PyYAML (config)\n- **AI/ML**: langchain, langgraph, ollama, neonize\n- **Data**: pandas, openpyxl (Excel), sqlalchemy (ORM)\n- **PDF**: fpdf2, matplotlib (histograms)\n- **Web**: fastapi, uvicorn (health endpoints)\n- **Utilities**: loguru (structured logging), python-dotenv (env vars), tenacity (retries), Pillow (image ops)\n\n### 7. **Agent Workflow (LangGraph State Machine)**\nThe agent uses a 7-node graph:\n1. **load_context** → Fetch teacher profile & language preference from DB\n2. **plan** → Determine intent (image, confirmation, cancellation, or text query)\n3. **Conditional routing**:\n   - `handle_image` → OCR extraction, preview Excel update\n   - `handle_confirm` → Apply Excel update, generate PDF\n   - `handle_cancel` → Cancel pending action\n   - `handle_text` → Process other queries\n4. **finalize** → Prepare replies\n5. **END**\n\n### 8. **Health Endpoints**\n- `GET http://127.0.0.1:18789/healthz` - Full health snapshot (DB, Ollama status, WhatsApp connection)\n- `GET http://127.0.0.1:18789/readyz` - Readiness check (Ollama reachable)\n\n### 9. **Additional Notes**\n- **Anti-spam**: Rate limiting per teacher (30 messages / 5-min window)\n- **Data mutations**: Strict confirmation gate + automatic backups before Excel writes\n- **Audit logging**: All actions logged to SQLite with timestamps\n- **Extensibility**: Skills can be added to `./skills/` and registered as LangChain tools\n- **Docker support**: `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` provided for containerization\n\nThis is a sophisticated, production-ready system combining WhatsApp messaging, local AI/vision, data persistence, backup safety, and comprehensive logging/auditing."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a41935e9b6d71fcfa (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 35915\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 31578</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"bc6e52f3-f888-4016-aa3b-82d3647ebc8c","timestamp":"2026-02-21T14:46:47.869Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the project at C:\\Users\\johnm\\gradeBot\\teacher-grade-agent thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. What kind of project this is (language, framework)\n2. How it's meant to be run (look for package.json, requirements.txt, Makefile, README, docker-compose, etc.)\n3. Any configuration files, environment variables, or setup steps required\n4. Entry points (main files, scripts, etc.)\n\nBe very thorough - check all config files, READMEs, and any documentation about running the project.","agentId":"a41935e9b6d71fcfa","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary of the project:\n\n## Project Exploration Summary\n\n### 1. **Project Type & Language**\n- **Language**: Python 3.12+\n- **Framework**: Multi-framework architecture:\n  - **LangGraph**: Stateful agentic workflow orchestration\n  - **FastAPI**: Health/readiness endpoints\n  - **LangChain**: Tool definition and integration\n  - **Neonize**: WhatsApp client (MD protocol)\n  - **Ollama**: Local multimodal AI (vision + language)\n\n### 2. **Purpose**\nTeacherGradeAgent is a **local-first, production-grade AI assistant for teachers** that:\n- Receives grade-sheet photos via WhatsApp\n- Performs OCR using locally-hosted `qwen3-vl:30b` model (multimodal vision-language)\n- Requests explicit confirmation before data mutations\n- Updates Excel workbooks with automatic backups\n- Generates PDF reports with customizable profiles\n- Replies via WhatsApp with confirmation and report paths\n\n### 3. **How to Run**\n\n#### Prerequisites\n- Python 3.12+\n- Ollama installed locally with `qwen3-vl:30b` model pulled\n- WhatsApp account (for QR pairing on first run)\n\n#### Installation Steps\n```bash\ncd teacher-grade-agent\npython -m venv .venv\n# Windows: .venv\\Scripts\\activate\n# macOS/Linux: source .venv/bin/activate\npip install -r requirements.txt\nollama pull qwen3-vl:30b\nollama serve  # in another terminal\n```\n\n#### Starting the Service\n```bash\npython main.py start     # Start service (auto-pairs WhatsApp on first run)\npython main.py status   # Check status\npython main.py backup   # Manual backup\n```\n\n#### Docker (Optional)\n```bash\ndocker compose up --build -d\n```\n\n#### Systemd Service (Linux, Optional)\nUse template file: `teacher-grade-agent.service.example`\n\n### 4. **Configuration Files & Environment Variables**\n\n#### Primary Config: `config.yaml`\nYAML-based hierarchical configuration covering:\n- App metadata (name, environment, timezone)\n- Directory paths (data, logs, reports, backups, excel, sessions, skills)\n- Database (SQLite path)\n- Ollama (base URL, model name, timeout, temperature)\n- WhatsApp (device name, session store, media dir, reconnect settings, admin numbers)\n- Rate limiting (30 messages per 300 seconds)\n- Agent settings (retries, OCR confidence threshold, pending action TTL, max rows per image)\n- Excel (workbook name, sheet name, required columns, auto-create flag)\n- Report generation (default PDF profile with toggles for cover, student table, histograms, etc.)\n- Logging (level, rotation, retention)\n- Health endpoint (enabled by default at 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n#### Environment Overrides: `.env.example`\nAll config settings can be overridden via environment variables prefixed with `TGA_`:\n- `TGA_CONFIG_PATH`\n- `TGA_OLLAMA_BASE_URL`, `TGA_OLLAMA_MODEL`\n- `TGA_DATABASE_SQLITE_PATH`\n- `TGA_PATHS_SESSION_DIR`, `TGA_PATHS_REPORTS_DIR`, `TGA_PATHS_EXCEL_DIR`\n- `TGA_LOGGING_LEVEL`\n- `TGA_AGENT_DEFAULT_LANGUAGE_MODE`\n- `TGA_HEALTH_ENABLED`, `TGA_HEALTH_HOST`, `TGA_HEALTH_PORT`\n\n### 5. **Entry Points & Directory Structure**\n\n#### Main Entry Point\n**`main.py`** - CLI application with three commands:\n- `start`: Launch the WhatsApp service (includes health server)\n- `status`: Check system health (DB, Ollama, model availability)\n- `backup`: Create manual backup of Excel files and audit logs\n\n#### Source Code Layout\n```\nsrc/\n├── config.py              # Settings loading (YAML + env overrides via Pydantic)\n├── whatsapp/\n│   ├── client.py         # Neonize-based WhatsApp client (event-driven)\n│   └── handlers.py       # Message processing & routing\n├── agent/\n│   ├── graph.py          # LangGraph workflow (7-node state machine)\n│   ├── tools.py          # LangChain StructuredTool definitions\n│   ├── prompts.py        # System/user prompts for planning & tooling\n│   └── state.py          # TypedDict schemas for agent state\n├── tools/\n│   ├── vision_ocr.py     # Ollama integration (qwen3-vl multimodal)\n│   ├── excel_handler.py  # XLSX read/write with backups\n│   ├── report_generator.py # PDF generation with matplotlib/fpdf2\n│   └── utils.py          # Helpers (token parsing, backups, etc.)\n└── db/\n    └── models.py         # SQLAlchemy ORM (Teacher, PendingAction, AuditLog)\n```\n\n#### Data Directory\nAll runtime artifacts stored in `./data/`:\n- `./data/excel/` - Teacher Excel workbooks\n- `./data/reports/` - Generated PDF reports\n- `./data/backups/` - Automatic & manual workbook backups\n- `./data/sessions/` - Neonize WhatsApp session DB and media\n- `./data/logs/` - Application logs (rotated, 14-day retention)\n- `./data/teacher_grade_agent.db` - SQLite (audit logs, teacher profiles, pending actions)\n\n#### Optional Skills Directory\n`./skills/` - Extensible Python modules for custom skills (registered in `src/agent/tools.py`)\n\n### 6. **Key Dependencies** (from requirements.txt)\n- **Core**: typer (CLI), pydantic (settings), PyYAML (config)\n- **AI/ML**: langchain, langgraph, ollama, neonize\n- **Data**: pandas, openpyxl (Excel), sqlalchemy (ORM)\n- **PDF**: fpdf2, matplotlib (histograms)\n- **Web**: fastapi, uvicorn (health endpoints)\n- **Utilities**: loguru (structured logging), python-dotenv (env vars), tenacity (retries), Pillow (image ops)\n\n### 7. **Agent Workflow (LangGraph State Machine)**\nThe agent uses a 7-node graph:\n1. **load_context** → Fetch teacher profile & language preference from DB\n2. **plan** → Determine intent (image, confirmation, cancellation, or text query)\n3. **Conditional routing**:\n   - `handle_image` → OCR extraction, preview Excel update\n   - `handle_confirm` → Apply Excel update, generate PDF\n   - `handle_cancel` → Cancel pending action\n   - `handle_text` → Process other queries\n4. **finalize** → Prepare replies\n5. **END**\n\n### 8. **Health Endpoints**\n- `GET http://127.0.0.1:18789/healthz` - Full health snapshot (DB, Ollama status, WhatsApp connection)\n- `GET http://127.0.0.1:18789/readyz` - Readiness check (Ollama reachable)\n\n### 9. **Additional Notes**\n- **Anti-spam**: Rate limiting per teacher (30 messages / 5-min window)\n- **Data mutations**: Strict confirmation gate + automatic backups before Excel writes\n- **Audit logging**: All actions logged to SQLite with timestamps\n- **Extensibility**: Skills can be added to `./skills/` and registered as LangChain tools\n- **Docker support**: `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` provided for containerization\n\nThis is a sophisticated, production-ready system combining WhatsApp messaging, local AI/vision, data persistence, backup safety, and comprehensive logging/auditing."}],"totalDurationMs":31578,"totalTokens":35915,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3801,"cache_read_input_tokens":30168,"output_tokens":1939,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3801,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"609521ac-d62d-4138-bfc4-ba400baa1b69"}
